1279B 101st Legislative Session 1279
2026 South Dakota Legislature
House Bill 1279
AMENDME NT 1279B
FOR THE INTRODUCED BILL
Introduced by: Representative Mortenson
1 An Act to permit technical college employees to join the state health plan.
2 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF SOUTH DAKOTA:
3 Section 1. That § 3-6E-1 be AMENDED:
4 3-6E-1. The bureau may establish a benefits plan for plan-eligible employees of
5 the state and technical college employees, pursuant to section 2 of this Act. The plan may
6 either be self-funded or established as a group health insurance program. The plan may
7 provide for group health coverage against the financial cost of hospital, surgical,
8 pharmacy, and medical treatment and care, and any other coverage or benefits the human
9 resources commissioner determines is appropriate and desirable. The human resources
10 commissioner may include a flexible benefit plan which that allows an employee to choose
11 the employee's own benefits or levels of coverage.
12 Section 2. That a NEW SECTION be added to chapter 3-6E:
13 Notwithstanding any other sections of law, a technical college employee may join
14 the plan on terms and conditions agreed upon by the human resources commissioner and
15 the president of the technical college.
16 Except as otherwise provided in this section, a technical college employee who
17 participates in the plan is considered a plan-eligible employee and a member of the plan
18 under this chapter.
19 In lieu of the monthly state contribution described in § 3-6E-8, the LEA, as defined
20 in § 13-39A-1, that employs a technical college employee shall contribute to the system
21 an amount equivalent to no less than the monthly contribution provided by the state for
22 other plan-eligible employees.
23 In lieu of a payroll deduction by the state, as described under § 3-6E-9, a technical
24 college employee enrolled participating in the plan shall may deduct from an employee's
Underscores indicate new language.
Overstrikes indicate deleted language.

1279B 2 1279
1 salary, and pay to the state treasurer any premium or contribution required by the human
2 resources commissioner, pursuant to § 3-6E-9.
3 A technical college or LEA, may not restrict a technical college employee from
4 joining the plan.
5 The human resources commissioner shall promulgate rules for the administration
6 of this section.
7 For the purpose of this chapter "technical college employee" means an individual
8 who is a permanent employee of a technical college in this state, as listed in § 13-39A-
9 42, and who is scheduled to work twenty or more hours a week, at least six months of
10 each year.
11 Section 3. That § 3-6E-8 be AMENDED:
12 3-6E-8. The State of South DakotaThe state shall either make a monthly
13 contribution to the system or otherwise provide for the amount necessary to make
14 payment to the system for the full single rate monthly health insurance premium or
15 contribution for the plan with the lowest actuarial value for each plan-eligible employee,
16 except for a technical college employee, pursuant to section 2 of this Act. This amount
17 shall must be transmitted to the account of the state employees' benefits plan in the Office
18 of the State Treasurer. The state treasurer, after making a record of the receipts, shall
19 credit the plan with an amount equal to that remitted or otherwise provided. Costs beyond
20 this amount for other plans offered by the state shall must be paid by the employee
21 through premiums. After the contribution has been assigned to the plan, the bureau shall
22 disburse the contribution in accordance with this chapter and the rules promulgated
23 pursuant to chapter 1-26 by the human resources commissioner.
24 Section 4. That § 3-6E-9 be AMENDED:
25 3-6E-9. The State of South DakotaThe state shall deduct on each payroll of a
26 member, except for a member who is a technical college employee pursuant to section 2
27 of this Act, for each payroll period, the amount of the contribution or premium, including
28 any administrative expense. The state shall make deductions from salaries of plan-eligible
29 employees, except for technical college employees, pursuant to section 2 of this Act, and
30 shall transmit monthly the amount specified to be deducted to the state treasurer. The
31 state treasurer, after making a record of receipts, shall credit the benefits plan with an
32 amount equal to that remitted by the state. After the credit has been assigned to the
33 benefits plan, the human resources commissioner shall disburse credit in accordance with
