1 this chapter and the rules promulgated pursuant to chapter 1-26 by the human resources
2 commissioner.
3 Section 5. That § 3-6E-13 be AMENDED:
4 3-6E-13. The human resources commissioner is responsible for the administration
5 of this chapter and shall promulgate rules required for the effective administration of the
6 provisions of this chapter pursuant to chapter 1-26. The rules may must be promulgated
7 in the following areas:
8 (1) To establish what benefits will are to be offered pursuant to this chapter;
9 (2) Participation in the plan by employees, retired employees, technical college
10 employees, and dependents;
11 (3) Procedures for election of coverage;
12 (4) Effective dates of coverage if not specified by statute;
13 (5) Termination of coverage;
14 (6) Changes in dependent coverage;
15 (7) Collection of premiums and contributions;
16 (8) To coordinate the benefits plan with the health insurance plan authorized in this
17 chapter; and
18 (9) Other provisions as required to meet federal law.
19 Section 6. This Act is effective beginning July 1, 2027.
